# Devbench / ConfigForge

> Nine essential developer tools + **ConfigForge** — a multi-format config file converter supporting **9 formats** (JSON, YAML, TOML, XML, CSV, INI, .env, HCL, .properties). All offline, all private.

## Features

### ConfigForge (`devbench cf`)
Convert config files between any of 9 formats — bidirectionally, offline, with comment preservation.

```bash
# Install
pip install devbench-cf

# Convert JSON to YAML
devbench cf convert config.json config.yaml

# Convert TOML to .env for container builds
devbench cf convert pyproject.toml settings.env

# Batch convert all JSON files to YAML
devbench cf convert --batch "*.json" --to yaml

# Detect format automatically
devbench cf detect config.unknown
```

### Developer Tools (CLI + Detector)
The `devbench` CLI includes 9 tools plus clipboard auto-detection:

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `json` | Format, validate, and minify JSON |
| `base64` | Encode/decode base64 data |
| `jwt` | Decode JWT tokens |
| `hash` | Generate hashes (MD5, SHA) |
| `url` | URL encode/decode with query string parsing |
| `timestamp` | Convert Unix timestamps ↔ human dates |
| `uuid` | Generate v4 UUIDs (single or batch) |
| `diff` | Side-by-side text comparison |
| `cf` | ConfigForge — multi-format config conversion |

Clipboard auto-detection intelligently recognizes JSON, JWT, URLs, timestamps, base64, and config formats from any pasted text.

### Supported Formats (ConfigForge)

| Format | Read | Write | Comment Preservation |
|--------|------|-------|---------------------|
| JSON | ✅ | ✅ | N/A (no comments in JSON) |
| YAML | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| TOML | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| XML | ✅ | ✅ | ⚠️ Structural comments |
| CSV | ✅ | ✅ | N/A |
| INI | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| .env | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| HCL | ✅ | ✅ | ⚠️ Limited (hcl2 dep) |
| .properties | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install from source
git clone https://github.com/apeters247/devbench
cd devbench
pip install -e .

# Or install the package directly
pip install devbench-cf

# Try it
devbench cf convert --help
devbench detect '{"hello": "world"}'
```

## Test Suite

```bash
cd devbench
pip install -e ".[test]"
python -m pytest tests/ -q --tb=line
```

Current status: **574 tests passing, 7 skipped, 2 xfailed — 0 failures.**

